============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is capitalism?
A1: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q2: What is the Pythagorean theorem?
A2: In a right triangle: a² + b² = c², where c is the
     hypotenuse. If a=3 and b=4, then c=5. Used in
     navigation, construction, and computer graphics.

Q3: What is evolution?
A3: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q4: What is the greenhouse effect?
A4: Greenhouse gases (CO2, methane) trap heat radiated from
     Earth's surface. Natural effect warms Earth; human
     emissions intensify it causing climate change.

Q5: What is relativity?
A5: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

